WEBVTT

00:05.890 --> 00:06.891
Now's the time.

00:10.174 --> 00:11.315
The time to build.

00:14.739 --> 00:16.460
Not everything that's built endures.

00:17.421 --> 00:19.223
Not everything that's built remains.

00:20.304 --> 00:21.806
Some things fall under pressure.

00:22.666 --> 00:24.228
Some things fade with time.

00:25.769 --> 00:27.691
Will what we build now endure?

00:29.773 --> 00:34.578
Will what we build speak through the next generation.

00:36.098 --> 00:39.845
We must be diligent, determined, and dedicated.

00:40.586 --> 00:45.095
After all, his church must be built to last.

00:47.279 --> 00:48.060
Man, amen.

00:48.100 --> 00:48.781
Good morning.

00:48.801 --> 00:51.126
Wow, happy new year.

00:52.128 --> 00:55.213
What an exciting first Sunday of the year this is.

00:55.834 --> 00:57.778
Man, a lot of times, many years,

00:57.890 --> 01:02.257
On the first Sunday of the year is kind of a kind of a draggy Sunday.

01:02.678 --> 01:08.146
Few people show up because they're kind of still sleepy from a busy, busy weekend and everything going on.

01:08.166 --> 01:15.178
But you all showed up today, but better yet, the spirit of God, the presence of the Lord is in this place today.

01:15.218 --> 01:15.999
Amen.

01:16.520 --> 01:16.840
Amen.

01:17.021 --> 01:22.930
I believe that God wants to speak into our hearts in a real personal way today.

01:23.746 --> 01:33.290
If you're here, perhaps you're checking out, encounter church for the first time, you saw a bunch of cars in the parking lot, or you saw a giant E on the building, you thought, what does that even mean?

01:33.590 --> 01:36.197
And you pulled in, I'm glad that you're here.

01:36.878 --> 01:39.986
Because I believe that God has something in store of

01:40.098 --> 01:44.183
For you, I believe that you are here for such a time as this.

01:44.323 --> 01:48.128
I believe that God wants to show up in your situation.

01:48.409 --> 01:50.371
God wants to speak into your life.

01:50.631 --> 01:52.894
God wants to lead you in a new direction.

01:52.934 --> 02:02.807
You see today, we're kicking off a brand new series that's gonna lay the foundation of where we're going as a church over this next year.

02:02.827 --> 02:05.170
We're simply calling the series built

02:05.378 --> 02:06.019
to last.

02:06.119 --> 02:08.183
Why are we calling it built to last?

02:08.203 --> 02:12.249
Because I don't know about you, but I don't like to build things that don't last long.

02:13.191 --> 02:17.077
I had a staff member several years ago, and he kind of had that same mentality.

02:17.097 --> 02:20.803
Anytime he built something, it was done solid.

02:20.843 --> 02:30.098
He built a small stage for a room upstairs, and as we were remodeling several years ago, we started moving that stage to a new area, found out that he had put

02:30.338 --> 02:36.926
these really super long screws into the ground so that that stage didn't move and they were everywhere.

02:38.348 --> 02:44.495
The stage was only this tall, but it was not moving, it was built to last.

02:45.156 --> 03:00.274
And you know, I look at our lives and I think sometimes we're guilty of building our personal spiritual lives with God, but we're only using like a half inch screw and we're trying to build into a foundation

03:00.386 --> 03:07.440
But the problem is somebody kicks that board and we kind of fall out of place because we're not really anchored.

03:07.460 --> 03:09.650
We're not built to last.

03:10.018 --> 03:33.682
I believe God wants us as a church to be built to last to the point that when the winds blow, when the struggles come, when the difficulty comes up against us, when we face the opposition, when the enemy raises his evil head, suddenly we're standing firm on a foundation and we're not moving because we have those lag bolts, not the little wimpy bolts, but the lag bolts into the foundation of God.

03:34.402 --> 03:34.822
Amen.

03:34.843 --> 03:36.985
Hey, I can't preach yet because that's not even my notes.

03:37.305 --> 03:39.067
Hey, let me introduce myself.

03:39.127 --> 03:40.309
My name is Pastor Chris.

03:40.769 --> 03:43.172
I am honored that you're with us today.

03:44.093 --> 03:52.843
This is a monumental day because this is a day where we, we open up the curtains, we pull back and unveil kind of where we're headed.

03:53.104 --> 04:00.372
And over the next few weeks, we're not going to do it all today because I want to spend the next four weeks looking at this series built to last.

04:00.392 --> 04:02.194
And I'm going to encourage you be here.

04:02.626 --> 04:06.032
We are at a very exciting time as a church.

04:06.412 --> 04:11.180
We are up about 90 or 100 people since last year at this time.

04:11.962 --> 04:12.863
Yeah, amen.

04:12.883 --> 04:13.464
Amen.

04:13.484 --> 04:23.181
In 2025, we had a little over 120 people give their life to Jesus Christ, commit themselves for eternity to Him.

04:23.241 --> 04:23.922
Amen?

04:24.994 --> 04:36.158
We are within a month and a half, two months of sticking a big old shovel called a backhoe in the ground to build an 18,000 square foot expansion on a 12,000 square foot building.

04:36.900 --> 04:38.323
Come on, God's good.

04:38.383 --> 04:39.706
God's good.

04:39.746 --> 04:40.548
Come on, stay with me.

04:40.628 --> 04:41.650
God's good.

04:41.826 --> 04:44.549
Sometimes we forget the goodness of God.

04:44.750 --> 04:46.992
We get comfortable in where we are.

04:47.193 --> 04:49.656
We get comfortable in doing what we do.

04:49.936 --> 04:55.903
Sometimes we even get comfortable doing ministry and we forget that without God, it's not possible.

04:58.366 --> 05:01.770
If you're hanging out with us today, I want to encourage you, keep coming back.

05:02.692 --> 05:08.018
Those of you that are watching online, if there's any way, come hang out with us.

05:08.322 --> 05:09.544
I know that it's easy.

05:09.564 --> 05:11.527
I know it's convenient just to watch online.

05:11.547 --> 05:13.590
And some of you are there because you can't get here.

05:13.891 --> 05:15.493
And man, enjoy this moment.

05:15.533 --> 05:17.376
Enjoy the online service.

05:17.396 --> 05:23.285
But if you can get here, there's something about being in this room with other believers.

05:23.305 --> 05:27.632
There's something about, hey, I don't know about you, but I was getting excited up here this morning.

05:28.653 --> 05:34.202
I know, I'm hoping that in this area, you guys are all probably thinking, pastor is crazy today.

05:34.262 --> 05:36.946
It could be because I changed my coffee.

05:37.346 --> 05:41.092
I don't know, I don't know, or it could just be the presence of God.

05:41.132 --> 05:41.993
I think it's that one.

05:42.033 --> 05:52.850
Instead, hey, I want to talk to you today about this idea of building something to last.

05:52.870 --> 06:03.346
You see, the goal of this series is to lay the foundation of a solid building that we will build upon for generations to come, not just a physical building.

06:04.034 --> 06:08.002
Yeah, over the next several weeks, we're going to talk about a building on and off.

06:08.804 --> 06:12.411
But truly, it's more than just a physical building.

06:12.431 --> 06:13.995
That's just a venue.

06:14.015 --> 06:17.121
That's just an area for us to gather.

06:17.161 --> 06:19.987
What we're going to build is build his church.

06:21.029 --> 06:22.953
We're going to build it from the ground up.

06:22.973 --> 06:25.298
We're going to say, God, whatever you want us,

06:25.442 --> 06:33.114
to do it, and I wanna use a scripture, a conversation really, that Jesus was having with a man by the name of Simon.

06:33.174 --> 06:41.367
We oftentimes refer to him as Peter, and this is the moment in time where there was a name change for Simon.

06:41.908 --> 06:44.372
Look what it says in Matthew chapter 16.

06:45.233 --> 06:53.586
It says, when Jesus came to the region of Caesarea Philippi, he asked his disciples, who do people say

06:53.858 --> 06:55.100
that the Son of Man is.

06:56.321 --> 07:03.490
Well, they replied, some say that you're John the Baptist, some others say that you're Elijah, and yet others say Jeremiah, or one of the other prophets.

07:04.692 --> 07:09.698
Then he asked them, but who do you say that I am?

07:10.379 --> 07:13.203
Let me pause for just a moment and kind of interject here.

07:13.483 --> 07:19.491
Sometimes we're really guilty of giving a pad answer of what other people say.

07:19.551 --> 07:21.714
Well, some say this,

07:22.370 --> 07:30.058
Some believe that, but I wonder, what is the lag bolt that you're using to dig into the foundation?

07:31.420 --> 07:36.605
What is anchoring you to the foundation of Jesus Christ?

07:36.625 --> 07:39.068
Jesus looked at them and he asked a very personal question.

07:39.709 --> 07:47.577
It's almost as if he says, yeah, I know what they're saying, but I'm not as much concerned about them as I am with you.

07:47.597 --> 07:51.922
And he says, but who do you say that I am?

07:52.130 --> 07:56.955
Simon Peter answered, you are the Messiah, the son of the living God.

07:58.096 --> 08:03.522
Jesus replied, you are blessed, Simon, Son of John, because my father in heaven has revealed this to you.

08:04.103 --> 08:06.305
You did not learn this from any human being.

08:07.286 --> 08:12.072
Now I say to you that you are Peter, which means rock.

08:12.092 --> 08:17.938
And upon this rock, I will build my church and all the powers of hell will not conquer it.

08:23.842 --> 08:26.866
There's a couple things that are very important that we take note of this morning.

08:27.708 --> 08:35.058
One thing I like to do when I'm diving into a message is I'll kind of look at different words in that scripture.

08:35.079 --> 08:40.867
And I'll go back to the original language and I know it's kind of a maybe a nerdy thing to do, but hey, it's okay.

08:40.927 --> 08:42.550
White and nerdy, it's okay.

08:43.791 --> 08:45.474
Some of you remember the 80s song, it's okay.

08:46.836 --> 08:48.338
It's all right, you can chuckle.

08:49.890 --> 09:01.223
But as I begin to look at this, I look at the word rock because he says, Simon, you are Peter, which means rock, and upon this rock, and I wondered, is rock in both of those contexts?

09:01.443 --> 09:02.904
Does it mean the same thing?

09:03.585 --> 09:13.937
And I realize that the first time when he said Simon, you are Peter, which means rock, that is actually the word petros, and it means little rock.

09:15.578 --> 09:18.802
Just a small little stone, nothing major.

09:18.882 --> 09:24.269
So Simon Peter is not the rock, but a small rock, perhaps even amongst many.

09:24.289 --> 09:31.938
And then he says, upon this rock, which is Petra, I will build my church.

09:31.958 --> 09:33.960
And here the word Petra goes a little deeper.

09:34.080 --> 09:37.224
It means a massive rock.

09:37.284 --> 09:39.988
Peter, you are a small rock.

09:40.028 --> 09:48.498
You are, you are a bloody small stone, but upon this rock, this massive rock, I will build my church.

09:49.154 --> 10:02.551
And it's important for us to clarify here that Jesus is not saying that the church is built upon Peter, but rather the church is built upon the solid firm foundation of Jesus Christ.

10:03.272 --> 10:09.700
We are building upon the confession that Jesus is in fact Christ, the son of the living God.

10:09.800 --> 10:17.330
Peter even declared this in first Peter chapter two, where he says, Jesus is the living cornerstone.

10:19.106 --> 10:22.051
He's the living cornerstone of God's temple.

10:22.592 --> 10:25.877
Now we're gonna talk more about this in just a few minutes.

10:25.897 --> 10:42.043
But you see, the moment we begin or even try to build the church on any person, any ministry, any group other than Jesus, the foundation will quickly crumble.

10:42.063 --> 10:46.130
It's like we have the formula for the concrete wrong.

10:47.170 --> 10:52.797
Come on, how many of you know if you don't mix the concrete right, it's not gonna last.

10:52.817 --> 11:00.687
It's not going to cure properly, it's not going to sustain properly, it's not going to hold the pressure properly.

11:00.747 --> 11:11.921
And sometimes, many times, the church world builds upon an individual or a group of people rather than building upon the true foundation of Jesus Christ.

11:11.961 --> 11:15.826
We've watched it historically time and time again.

11:16.578 --> 11:18.140
the church begins to crumble.

11:19.341 --> 11:33.254
But when we build his church, when we build it on Christ, our solid rock, then and only then, will it be built to last?

11:34.395 --> 11:43.584
Come on, always sing the song for years, on Christ the solid, rock I stand, all of the ground is sinking sand.

11:43.945 --> 11:45.426
But the problem was,

11:45.986 --> 11:51.795
Many times it was just a song we sang, but not a value we held to.

11:55.020 --> 12:01.931
We were busy building upon our ministry, our department of the church.

12:02.892 --> 12:11.826
Could I just tell you how many times I've seen church people bicker because they thought their department was more important than another department?

12:12.482 --> 12:15.186
Can I just tell you, here's my belief on that.

12:15.206 --> 12:15.907
Are you ready for this?

12:16.608 --> 12:17.349
That's stupid.

12:20.834 --> 12:22.897
My wife's not here this morning, so I'm kind of unhinged.

12:24.900 --> 12:25.962
Yeah, she's not feeling well.

12:26.022 --> 12:28.906
So, you know, you don't know what's going to come out of this mouth this morning.

12:29.046 --> 12:42.386
She's not down here going, but if we would just really step back for a moment and say, Lord, less of me, more of you.

12:43.810 --> 12:52.738
And that doesn't just go for myself, that doesn't just go for our leadership team, but it goes for every single person in this room.

12:52.778 --> 12:58.244
God, if you would just help us, Lord, to step back and give you full control.

12:58.284 --> 13:06.792
Because when we build upon the foundation of Jesus Christ, then and only then will it be built to last.

13:06.812 --> 13:13.458
So our theme for 2026, some of you have probably figured it out or you looked at this new shirts in the lobby,

13:14.242 --> 13:17.547
is build his church, build his church.

13:17.647 --> 13:24.818
That's what we're going to use as our launching pad or our foundation to build upon all of this year.

13:25.559 --> 13:32.851
Now, we're not looking at just building a building, we're not looking at building a name for ourselves or even attempting to be recognized.

13:32.971 --> 13:42.866
Our goal is to build his church upon the rock, the Petra, the massive stone that the gates of hell

13:43.074 --> 13:46.558
will not be able to shake or even conquer.

13:47.740 --> 13:52.405
Come on, we don't want to just build a church that has a fancy Sunday morning service.

13:53.226 --> 14:00.415
We don't want to just build a church that has a great youth group or a great kids ministry or an incredible worship team.

14:00.435 --> 14:02.077
And I believe we have those.

14:04.160 --> 14:09.546
But I believe that we need to build a church that's founded upon the Word of God.

14:11.629 --> 14:12.850
Build a church.

14:13.250 --> 14:14.533
that's founded on prayer.

14:14.573 --> 14:17.701
And right now we're in a 21 day prayer and fasting.

14:17.721 --> 14:20.609
If you haven't decided to jump in, it starts today.

14:20.649 --> 14:23.356
Now is the time to jump in.

14:23.396 --> 14:24.518
Spend time.

14:24.559 --> 14:25.621
There's a prayer guide.

14:25.641 --> 14:26.925
It's paper copy.

14:26.965 --> 14:27.887
It's online.

14:28.228 --> 14:28.990
It's available.

14:29.250 --> 14:30.674
Participate in that.

14:30.818 --> 14:40.091
fast in this season, fast for the church that we can build the church that God will use and the gates of hell cannot shake and cannot conquer.

14:40.312 --> 14:42.395
But I'm gonna challenge you today.

14:42.835 --> 14:45.980
Don't just be a spectator in this season.

14:48.804 --> 14:49.926
But let's build his church.

14:50.226 --> 14:54.532
Did you know that as you're building things, it goes a lot faster when you have people?

14:56.515 --> 14:58.418
I kinda learned that this week.

14:58.882 --> 15:04.489
So as a staff, we take a week between Christmas and New Year's off.

15:04.589 --> 15:08.754
So normally my family and I, we go to Branson and we hang out at Branson this year.

15:09.015 --> 15:10.036
We decided to stay home.

15:10.917 --> 15:14.181
So my wife said, hey, if we're staying home, I got some things you should do.

15:14.221 --> 15:16.804
That's so nice of her.

15:17.866 --> 15:18.386
Yeah.

15:18.907 --> 15:21.851
So I had to rip out carpet and tile.

15:21.891 --> 15:24.594
And by the way, if you ever lay tile,

15:25.890 --> 15:27.993
because ripping that stuff out is not easy.

15:28.294 --> 15:43.437
So I'm ripping out tile, I'm ripping out carpet, I'm cleaning out some drywall, I'm prepping floors, I'm taking up tack strips and I'm putting new flooring and then I get to the end of the week and one of the guys in church calls and said, hey, are you still working on your project?

15:43.457 --> 15:51.570
I said, almost done, but I have one area left and he came over and we knocked out in the day what would have taken me probably a day and a half by myself.

15:53.026 --> 15:59.312
I know there's others that volunteered to help, and I apologize, I should have used help, but how have you guys know I can do it?

15:59.352 --> 16:02.716
It's what we do, right?

16:03.817 --> 16:10.103
I realized I got muscles I didn't know I had, and I also realized I'm not 21 anymore.

16:10.143 --> 16:12.105
Where was I?

16:12.125 --> 16:15.709
I got off track and really preoccupied there.

16:17.390 --> 16:21.234
To build his church, we must rest on the fact

16:21.826 --> 16:24.351
that Jesus is who He said He was.

16:25.272 --> 16:27.436
He is who others said He was.

16:27.476 --> 16:33.127
And He is who He proves to be time and time again.

16:33.347 --> 16:39.478
To build His church is more than just a building expansion or even a renovation.

16:39.999 --> 16:41.382
It's building people.

16:42.083 --> 16:43.666
It's developing leaders.

16:43.746 --> 16:45.288
It's reaching the broken.

16:45.589 --> 16:46.851
It's mending the lives.

16:47.051 --> 16:58.710
It's truly being the church inside these walls and outside these walls and setting a culture that God calls us to hold to.

17:00.313 --> 17:05.200
It's building on the one and only source that will last.

17:05.801 --> 17:11.250
But listen carefully, it will not happen by accident.

17:13.474 --> 17:25.355
Pastor Joe kind of alluded to it in the legacy-giving moment this morning, but we're not going to walk in here one day and go, well, look, we tripped into God's presence.

17:25.375 --> 17:27.399
We tripped into something that's going to last.

17:28.601 --> 17:33.490
It's going to require people like you and people like me that are intentional

17:33.730 --> 17:42.385
that have purpose, that have drive, that are dedicated, that are willing to sacrifice for something larger than themselves.

17:42.566 --> 17:47.374
We've got to build not just for ourselves, but for generations to come.

17:48.676 --> 17:49.999
I wonder, is it worth it?

17:51.802 --> 17:54.066
Absolutely, it's worth it.

17:54.658 --> 17:57.842
in light of eternity and the lives that will take with us.

17:58.143 --> 18:05.954
It's worth every moment, every sacrifice, every dollar, every conversation, every moment of intentionality.

18:07.416 --> 18:14.386
So today with that being said, I want to give you three truths that I want you to consider, even grasp today.

18:14.426 --> 18:15.347
Number one is this.

18:16.689 --> 18:18.431
Jesus is in charge.

18:19.573 --> 18:21.375
Therefore we must follow His lead.

18:22.878 --> 18:23.218
Come on.

18:24.674 --> 18:27.338
You know, one thing that I just, I do not like.

18:28.841 --> 18:31.966
I don't like it when someone is talking to me and I'm in the community.

18:32.327 --> 18:34.831
And they're like, over there at your church and I'm like, hitting on my church?

18:36.393 --> 18:38.557
Is it my, no, it's not my church.

18:38.577 --> 18:39.819
It didn't say church to Chris.

18:41.582 --> 18:42.463
This is not my church.

18:42.483 --> 18:43.305
This is his church.

18:44.707 --> 18:45.528
I'm just a vessel.

18:46.991 --> 18:51.538
I'm just a person for the season of time that he says, I want you here.

18:52.194 --> 18:55.560
Can I be honest with you, this wasn't my place where I thought I was gonna be.

18:55.600 --> 18:58.826
Isn't that oftentimes how God works?

18:59.807 --> 19:04.696
Man, I had another plan, but yet God said, huh, I got a better plan.

19:05.798 --> 19:07.701
Oh, and I'm so glad that he had a better plan.

19:08.542 --> 19:10.306
I'm so glad that he had a better plan.

19:10.887 --> 19:17.458
And we stepping into that plan and we've seen God do some incredible things, but Jesus is in charge therefore we must follow

19:17.602 --> 19:25.434
His elite, look what it says in verse 18, upon this rock, I, Jesus, will build my church.

19:26.075 --> 19:36.471
This short statement, small little statement, should be a massive relief for every one of us today in the room or even watching online.

19:36.491 --> 19:36.811
Why?

19:37.532 --> 19:41.559
Because we're not responsible for the building process.

19:42.901 --> 19:43.762
Isn't that great?

19:45.890 --> 19:51.476
But here's what we are responsible for, our obedience in the process.

19:53.318 --> 19:57.702
We're not responsible for making it happen.

19:57.742 --> 20:03.088
We're not responsible for every detail and we're not responsible for every idea.

20:03.448 --> 20:10.095
We're simply responsible for being obedient to his call, to his lead, to his command.

20:10.155 --> 20:12.658
So here's what we must understand.

20:13.058 --> 20:22.971
When Jesus made this statement, he was building upon this statement that Peter made in response to the question, who do you or who do people say that I am?

20:24.272 --> 20:28.798
So the first thing that we've got to establish is who do you say Jesus is?

20:30.861 --> 20:33.764
See, you can't build upon something you don't know anything about.

20:36.148 --> 20:41.234
I wonder in your personal life, I'm not talking about encounter church as a church, I know what we,

20:41.506 --> 20:46.451
I know the 16th fundamental truths of the similes of God that we hold tightly to.

20:46.752 --> 20:48.834
I know the unwavering truth.

20:48.874 --> 20:52.058
I know the mission of encounter church to love, reach and empower.

20:52.298 --> 20:56.643
I've got all of that, but I wonder today, for you, who is Jesus?

20:58.525 --> 21:03.570
I would challenge you in this season, in this time, as we're in the building process.

21:05.232 --> 21:10.738
Would you come to the place of understanding that He is Christ, the Son of the living God?

21:11.522 --> 21:13.864
He is the Savior of the world.

21:15.045 --> 21:15.746
He's your friend.

21:16.287 --> 21:17.087
He's your Redeemer.

21:18.248 --> 21:19.109
He's your everything.

21:19.710 --> 21:22.032
He's the one that can take you from darkness into the light.

21:22.212 --> 21:26.376
He's the one that has given you the authority to stand the ground.

21:26.576 --> 21:31.101
He's given the one that's given you the strength that when the winds begin to blow, you will not be wavered.

21:31.221 --> 21:35.945
He's that lag bolt in life that holds you firmly to the foundation.

21:36.146 --> 21:38.107
He is your everything.

21:38.167 --> 21:40.850
So who is Jesus?

21:41.122 --> 21:49.835
You see, if he's truly the foundation that we build upon, we must understand who he is and the Psalmist says it this way.

21:50.356 --> 21:57.847
Jesus is the stone that the builders rejected has now become the cornerstone.

21:58.869 --> 22:03.055
The stone that the builders rejected has now become the cornerstone.

22:03.236 --> 22:09.145
Jesus is the cornerstone of our lives and of the church.

22:09.165 --> 22:10.066
So what does that mean?

22:10.946 --> 22:18.956
Well, the cornerstone on a building serves as a symbolic but also a practical purpose for the building construction.

22:19.517 --> 22:28.248
Historically, the cornerstone was the first stone that was set in the construction of a masonry foundation.

22:29.289 --> 22:31.032
This is the practical side of things.

22:31.152 --> 22:32.153
It wasn't decorative.

22:32.674 --> 22:33.935
It was an optional.

22:33.955 --> 22:36.018
It was essential.

22:37.058 --> 22:41.584
It mattered for the fact that the cornerstone had to be perfectly square.

22:41.624 --> 22:43.927
It had to be level.

22:43.987 --> 22:44.588
Why?

22:44.809 --> 22:48.774
Because everything else would align to it.

22:50.677 --> 22:58.467
I learned the importance of the beginning being aligned properly this week as two different rooms.

22:58.507 --> 23:06.258
I was laying floatable flooring and I realized that first row had to be

23:06.498 --> 23:07.159
straight.

23:08.400 --> 23:11.803
If that first row was off, the rest of the room was a mess.

23:13.445 --> 23:18.209
So it seemed like that first row took forever to do.

23:19.411 --> 23:27.138
But I understand now the importance and we look at our relationship with Christ and I understand that it's going to take time.

23:28.419 --> 23:35.346
It's going to take moments of dedication of getting to know Him, allowing His Word to be

23:35.586 --> 23:38.410
rooted inside of who we are.

23:39.773 --> 23:58.482
Getting to know His character, allowing the very nature that the Holy Spirit produces in us, according to Galatians 5, love, joy, peace, patience, kindness, goodness, faithfulness, gentleness, and self-control, not only to be placed in us, but to be nurtured so that they grow, that we overflow with the nature of God.

23:59.362 --> 24:01.945
It's not gonna happen by happenstance.

24:01.965 --> 24:07.390
It's not gonna happen by mistake, but we have got to build upon that cornerstone.

24:07.590 --> 24:12.555
If the cornerstone is off, then everything that follows will be off.

24:14.297 --> 24:24.387
Paul made this statement in 1 Corinthians, for knowing can lay any foundation other than the one who already have Jesus Christ.

24:25.968 --> 24:27.570
Jesus is our cornerstone.

24:28.802 --> 24:35.210
